HEADWORD: Commonness
<hw>Com"mon*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>State or quality
of being common or usual; <as>as, the <ex>commonness</ex> of
sunlight</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Triteness; meanness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commonplace</ent>⟦br⟧
